1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,740
Welcome to this reparenting meditation.

2
00:00:02,740 --> 00:00:09,133
This practice is about offering care,
protection, and presence to a younger

3
00:00:09,133 --> 00:00:10,170
part of you.

4
00:00:10,170 --> 00:00:16,362
It is not about forcing forgiveness,
forcing healing, or pretending the past

5
00:00:16,362 --> 00:00:17,600
did not matter.

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:23,156
It is about bringing Self-energy to a
part that may have needed more than it

7
00:00:23,156 --> 00:00:23,823
received.

8
00:00:23,823 --> 00:00:26,888
Begin by settling your body.

9
00:00:26,888 --> 00:00:29,489
Let yourself arrive slowly.

10
00:00:29,489 --> 00:00:31,765
Take a gentle breath in.

11
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:33,065
And breathe out.

12
00:00:33,065 --> 00:00:36,316
Feel the support underneath you.

13
00:00:48,316 --> 00:00:48,316
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

14
00:00:48,316 --> 00:00:52,263
Let your body know that you are here now.

15
00:00:52,263 --> 00:00:58,932
If at any point this feels like too much,
you can open your eyes, look around the

16
00:00:58,932 --> 00:01:02,433
room, move your body, or stop the
practice.

17
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:04,987
You are in charge of the pace.

18
00:01:04,987 --> 00:01:08,284
Now imagine a safe place inside.

19
00:01:20,284 --> 00:01:20,284
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

20
00:01:20,284 --> 00:01:22,188
It can be simple.

21
00:01:22,188 --> 00:01:23,488
A warm room.

22
00:01:23,488 --> 00:01:25,206
A quiet garden.

23
00:01:25,206 --> 00:01:26,924
A safe porch.

24
00:01:26,924 --> 00:01:28,364
A peaceful beach.

25
00:01:28,364 --> 00:01:30,965
A soft blanket.

26
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:34,820
Let the place form in whatever way it
wants to.

27
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:36,260
Now ask inside:

28
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:48,260
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

29
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:51,511
Is there a younger part of me that needs
care today?

30
00:02:03,511 --> 00:02:03,511
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

31
00:02:03,511 --> 00:02:07,551
If a younger part appears, notice them
gently.

32
00:02:07,551 --> 00:02:14,130
If no part appears, imagine sending care
to any younger part who may need it

33
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:14,656
later.

34
00:02:26,656 --> 00:02:26,656
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

35
00:02:26,656 --> 00:02:29,257
Notice this younger part.

36
00:02:29,257 --> 00:02:31,207
How old do they feel?

37
00:02:43,207 --> 00:02:43,207
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

38
00:02:43,207 --> 00:02:45,065
What are they wearing?

39
00:02:57,065 --> 00:02:57,065
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

40
00:02:57,065 --> 00:02:59,991
How close or far away are they?

41
00:03:11,991 --> 00:03:11,991
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

42
00:03:11,991 --> 00:03:14,824
What emotion do they seem to carry?

43
00:03:26,824 --> 00:03:26,824
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

44
00:03:26,824 --> 00:03:29,703
Before moving closer, ask:

45
00:03:29,703 --> 00:03:32,954
Would it be okay if I came a little
closer?

46
00:03:44,954 --> 00:03:44,954
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

47
00:03:44,954 --> 00:03:47,880
Respect whatever you sense.

48
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:52,013
If the part needs distance, stay at a
distance.

49
00:03:52,013 --> 00:03:55,450
Distance can still be caring.

50
00:03:55,450 --> 00:03:56,890
Now ask:

51
00:04:08,890 --> 00:04:08,890
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

52
00:04:08,890 --> 00:04:10,794
What did you need back then?

53
00:04:22,794 --> 00:04:22,794
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

54
00:04:22,794 --> 00:04:24,001
Listen.

55
00:04:42,001 --> 00:04:42,001
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

56
00:04:42,001 --> 00:04:44,091
Maybe they needed protection.

57
00:04:44,091 --> 00:04:45,438
Maybe comfort.

58
00:04:45,438 --> 00:04:47,946
Maybe someone to believe them.

59
00:04:47,946 --> 00:04:50,222
Maybe someone to stay.

60
00:04:50,222 --> 00:04:53,751
Maybe someone to explain that it was not
their fault.

61
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:56,816
Maybe someone to let them be a child.

62
00:04:56,816 --> 00:04:57,931
Now ask:

63
00:05:09,931 --> 00:05:09,931
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

64
00:05:09,931 --> 00:05:12,299
What do you need from me now?

65
00:05:24,299 --> 00:05:24,299
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

66
00:05:24,299 --> 00:05:27,875
You do not have to promise anything
impossible.

67
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:30,429
Offer what is true and gentle.

68
00:05:30,429 --> 00:05:31,636
You might say:

69
00:05:40,636 --> 00:05:40,636
<break time="3s" />

70
00:05:40,636 --> 00:05:42,679
I am here now.

71
00:05:42,679 --> 00:05:46,023
I want to understand what happened to
you.

72
00:05:46,023 --> 00:05:49,134
You did not deserve to be alone with
that.

73
00:05:49,134 --> 00:05:53,267
You do not have to carry this by yourself
right now.

74
00:05:53,267 --> 00:05:56,053
Notice how the younger part responds.

75
00:06:14,053 --> 00:06:14,053
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

76
00:06:14,053 --> 00:06:18,511
Now imagine offering the kind of care
that feels welcome.

77
00:06:30,511 --> 00:06:30,511
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

78
00:06:30,511 --> 00:06:33,344
Maybe sitting beside them.

79
00:06:33,344 --> 00:06:35,666
Maybe wrapping them in a blanket.

80
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:38,267
Maybe holding their hand.

81
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:47,267
<break time="3s" />

82
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:50,193
Maybe protecting the doorway.

83
00:06:50,193 --> 00:06:52,933
Maybe telling them they are not in
trouble.

84
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:55,069
Maybe letting them play.

85
00:06:55,069 --> 00:06:57,345
Maybe simply staying near.

86
00:06:57,345 --> 00:06:58,924
Now ask:

87
00:07:10,924 --> 00:07:10,924
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

88
00:07:10,924 --> 00:07:14,407
Is there anything you wish someone had
said to you?

89
00:07:26,407 --> 00:07:26,407
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

90
00:07:26,407 --> 00:07:30,819
If words come, imagine saying them
gently.

91
00:07:42,819 --> 00:07:42,819
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

92
00:07:42,819 --> 00:07:46,999
If no words come, simply offer presence.

93
00:07:46,999 --> 00:07:48,439
Now ask:

94
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:00,439
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

95
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:03,643
Would you like to show me anything about
what you went through?

96
00:08:15,643 --> 00:08:15,643
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

97
00:08:15,643 --> 00:08:22,377
If the part shows something, remember:
you do not have to go into every detail.

98
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,653
You can witness just enough.

99
00:08:24,653 --> 00:08:26,093
You can say:

100
00:08:26,093 --> 00:08:28,183
I believe this was hard.

101
00:08:28,183 --> 00:08:29,483
I am listening.

102
00:08:29,483 --> 00:08:31,851
We can go slowly.

103
00:08:31,851 --> 00:08:35,288
Now imagine bringing in more support.

104
00:08:47,288 --> 00:08:47,288
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

105
00:08:47,288 --> 00:08:49,192
Maybe your adult Self.

106
00:08:49,192 --> 00:08:50,725
Maybe a wise figure.

107
00:08:50,725 --> 00:08:52,908
Maybe light.

108
00:08:52,908 --> 00:08:55,648
Maybe a protective presence.

109
00:08:55,648 --> 00:08:58,295
Maybe other caring parts of you.

110
00:08:58,295 --> 00:09:02,382
Let this younger part know they do not
have to be alone.

111
00:09:02,382 --> 00:09:03,497
Now ask:

112
00:09:15,497 --> 00:09:15,497
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

113
00:09:15,497 --> 00:09:19,444
What would help you feel safer as we
close this practice?

114
00:09:31,444 --> 00:09:31,444
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

115
00:09:31,444 --> 00:09:33,859
Imagine offering that.

116
00:09:45,859 --> 00:09:45,859
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

117
00:09:45,859 --> 00:09:47,531
A safe room.

118
00:09:47,531 --> 00:09:49,667
A comforting object.

119
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:51,989
A protective boundary.

120
00:09:51,989 --> 00:09:55,611
A reminder that you can return.

121
00:09:55,611 --> 00:09:59,373
Now gently thank this younger part.

122
00:09:59,373 --> 00:10:00,627
You might say:

123
00:10:09,627 --> 00:10:09,627
<break time="3s" />

124
00:10:09,627 --> 00:10:12,228
Thank you for letting me know you.

125
00:10:12,228 --> 00:10:15,757
I will keep learning how to care for you.

126
00:10:15,757 --> 00:10:19,240
We can take this one step at a time.

127
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:22,955
Now begin to return to your present-day
body.

128
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,952
Feel your feet.

129
00:10:33,952 --> 00:10:33,952
<break time="3s" />

130
00:10:33,952 --> 00:10:35,299
Your hands.

131
00:10:35,299 --> 00:10:36,832
Your breath.

132
00:10:36,832 --> 00:10:39,572
The support underneath you.

133
00:10:39,572 --> 00:10:42,266
Look around the room if your eyes are
open.

134
00:10:42,266 --> 00:10:46,585
Or imagine the room around you if your
eyes are closed.

135
00:10:58,585 --> 00:10:58,585
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

136
00:10:58,585 --> 00:11:00,953
Orient to the present.

137
00:11:09,953 --> 00:11:09,953
<break time="3s" />

138
00:11:09,953 --> 00:11:12,693
Take one slow breath in.

139
00:11:21,693 --> 00:11:21,693
<break time="3s" />

140
00:11:21,693 --> 00:11:23,736
And let it out.

141
00:11:23,736 --> 00:11:27,730
When you are ready, return fully.

142
00:11:27,730 --> 00:11:33,922
Carry this connection gently. Reparenting
is not about becoming perfect. It is the

143
00:11:33,922 --> 00:11:40,037
steady practice of returning, listening,
protecting, and offering care one honest

144
00:11:40,037 --> 00:11:41,337
moment at a time.

